DIE Springbok-kaptein, Siya Kolisi, het op sy Instagram die man wie vir sy opvoeding betaal het bedank. Dit is die eerste keer wat Siya en die man, net bekend as Vincent, mekaar ontmoet het. Vincent het deur ‘n beursprogram vir Siya se opvoeding betaal. “Deur ‘n beursprogram het Vincent in honderde kinders in Suid-Afrika se toekoms belê. Dit het hy gedoen sonder om die meeste van hulle ooit te ontmoet,” skryf Siya. “Sonder die beursgeleentheid sou ek nooit wees waar ek vandag is nie. Hy het in my lewe geploeg, sonder om te weet wat die uitkoms gaan wees. Daarvoor is ek hom ewig dankbaar.” Siya en vroulief, Rachel, het in Amerika getoer, waar hulle Vincent ontmoet en met hom en sy vrou Annie tyd deur gebring het. Rachel and I have spent 2 days in NYC with Vincent and his wife Annie. Vincent is a fellow Grey boy and has invested in 100's of kids in SA through bursaries, majority of the time without ever meeting them. I was 1 of those kids. Without the opportunity, there is no way I'd be where I am today. He sowed into my life without ever knowing what would come from it, and I couldnt be more grateful. I'm so honored to have spent some time with him and his family. I’m so excited for the work we’re about to do in South Africa ???? together. Proverbs 11:25 A generous person will prosper; whoever refreshes others will be refreshed. A post shared by  Siya Kolisi (@siya_kolisi_the_bear) on Dec 29, 2019 at 9:28am PST 